# LightPrompt

LightPrompt is a privacy-first, multi-bot AI platform for soul-tech wellness, built with Next.js, Tailwind, Supabase, Sanity, and OpenAI.

## Features

- ChatGPT-style multi-bot UI
- Tiered access (Free, Paid, Enterprise)
- Secure, privacy-focused architecture
- Bot-to-bot awareness via user data (no cross-user data)
- Easy theming with Tailwind CSS

## Getting Started

### 1. Clone and install

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/lightprompt.git
cd lightprompt
npm install
```

### 2. Configure environment variables

Create a `.env` file and add:

```
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=...
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=...
OPENAI_API_KEY=...
NEXT_PUBLIC_SANITY_PROJECT_ID=...
NEXT_PUBLIC_SANITY_DATASET=...
```

### 3. Run locally

```bash
npm run dev
```

### 4. Deploy

- Push to GitHub and connect to Vercel.
- Set environment variables in Vercel dashboard.

## Privacy & Security

- Row Level Security (RLS) enforced in Supabase
- All secrets stored server-side and never exposed to the client
- No user data is shared outside of user context

